<h1 id="javascript">Javascript</h1>

<p>One of the more interesting things I learned today was that you can use the ternary operator (a.k.a question mark) to make code more succinct.</p>

<p>Instead of</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>function returnLarger(a, b) {
    if (a &gt; b) {
        return a 
    } else {
        return b
    }
}

</code></pre></div></div>

<p>You could just write</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>function returnLarger(a, b) {
    return a &gt; b ? a : b 
}    
</code></pre></div></div>
:ET